Pat Myrto (pat@rwing.UUCP) writes:

> /> >	On another note, has anyone written a virus for HP48 calculators?  :)
> /
> /> 	I have.  It's called a sledgehammer.  =)
> /
> /It doesn't spread. Therefore, by definition, it is not a virus. :-)

> No, but the hp-48 does after an attack...
> Does that mean the 48 turns into a virus?  :-)

Yes, that's it! Then, the sledgehammer conforms to the definition of
Dropper - not a virus by itself, but releases viruses, i.e., turns
other programs into viruses. That's it, a sledgehammer is a Dropper -
you drop it on a HP48 and the latter spreads - in tiny bits. :-)))

Regards,
Vesselin
